A little dump from my journey as a small business owner 💭✨

1)Picked a niche that didn’t feel like me
In the beginning, I chose what looked trendy—not what felt personal. It didn’t sit right, and the disconnect showed in everything I did.

2) Stayed behind the scenes too much
I thought letting the products or models do the talking was enough. But turns out—people connect more with you, the face and story behind the brand.

3) Tried to wear all the hats, all the time
I wanted to control everything—photos, packaging, sales, you name it. It only slowed me down and burned me out.

4) Didn’t test my own products
I wasn’t wearing my jewelry daily, so I missed flaws or improvements. Now, I wear what I create—and it’s helped me understand my pieces better.

5) Delayed starting because of fear
The brand lived in my notes app for way too long. I kept telling myself “not yet.” I wish I had just begun when the idea felt right.

6) Waited for the ‘perfect’ moment or launch
Truth: There’s no such thing. Perfect is just fear dressed up nicely. I should’ve launched messy and learnt on the way.

7) Tried to make something for everyone
In trying to please all, I attracted none. Now I know: the right people will find you when you stay true to your voice and vision.

8) Created from fear, not passion
Too often, I designed thinking “will people like this?” instead of “do I love this?” Big difference. Big lesson.

9) Neglected storytelling
I thought a pretty logo and product photos were enough. But it’s the story—your why—that actually makes people stay.

10) Forgot my brand is alive
It’s not just a business. It has its own energy. I’ve started treating it like a partner—talking to it, listening, letting it grow with me.

I know starting your own brand is exhausting and exciting at the same time !! 
So, do share this who needed it to hear right now 🫶🏿
